From: ConsoleRDP <consolerdp@local>
Date: Fri, 1 May 2026 11:35:00 -0500
Subject: Encode H.264 with Limited color range so mstsc renders darks correctly

[MS-RDPEGFX] section 3.1.5.5 specifies that the AVC444 progressive
H.264 video stream sent over the Graphics Pipeline must be encoded
with YUV420 *Limited* color range (Y: 16-235, UV: 16-240) per BT.601
or BT.709 conventions. Microsoft's Remote Desktop client (mstsc)
follows this spec strictly: the H.264 SPS VUI colour_range bit is
*ignored*, and the stream is always interpreted as Limited.

KRdp 6.6.4 unconditionally configures the PipeWire encoder to emit
Full range (Y: 0-255). The reason in the source comment is "so FFmpeg
decodes correctly", which was added for FreeRDP/wlfreerdp dev tooling
that does respect the VUI. With mstsc, the result is:

  * Server encodes "black" as Y=16 (limited's black), but the
    encoder is told it's full range, so the encoder doesn't
    pre-scale the input -- effectively shipping the linear output of
    the GPU into a Limited slot.
  * mstsc decodes Y=16 as 16/255 = 6.3% gray instead of 0% black.
  * All darks are visibly lifted: pure black on screen renders as
    #101010 in mstsc, near-black mid-tones blend into a uniform
    dark gray, and details in shadow regions are washed out.

Switching to ColorRange::Limited makes the encoder pre-scale RGB so
that pure black (0,0,0) ends up at Y=16 and pure white (255,255,255)
at Y=235, matching the decoder's expectation.

Tested with mstsc 10.0.x on Windows 11 against KRdp connected via
PlasmaScreencastV1Session: blacks are visibly black, mid-tones match
the physical display, no banding observed.

Side effect: any FreeRDP-based test client that ignored the VUI will
now see crushed blacks. Add a runtime override
(KRDP_COLOR_RANGE=full) if such a client is reintroduced.

---
 src/PlasmaScreencastV1Session.cpp | 5 ++++-
 src/PortalSession.cpp             | 5 ++++-
 2 files changed, 8 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

--- a/src/PlasmaScreencastV1Session.cpp
+++ b/src/PlasmaScreencastV1Session.cpp
@@ -225,7 +225,10 @@ void PlasmaScreencastV1Session::start()
         setLogicalSize(d->request->size());
         auto encodedStream = stream();
         encodedStream->setNodeId(nodeId);
         encodedStream->setEncodingPreference(PipeWireBaseEncodedStream::EncodingPreference::Speed);
-        encodedStream->setColorRange(PipeWireBaseEncodedStream::ColorRange::Full);
+        // Per [MS-RDPEGFX] 3.1.5.5, mstsc decodes the AVC444 H.264
+        // stream as YUV420 *Limited* range (Y: 16-235). Sending Full
+        // range produces lifted blacks (pure black -> #101010) on
+        // mstsc. Override via env KRDP_COLOR_RANGE=full if needed.
+        encodedStream->setColorRange(qEnvironmentVariable("KRDP_COLOR_RANGE") == QStringLiteral("full")
+                                         ? PipeWireBaseEncodedStream::ColorRange::Full
+                                         : PipeWireBaseEncodedStream::ColorRange::Limited);
         encodedStream->setEncoder(PipeWireEncodedStream::H264Baseline);
         connect(encodedStream, &PipeWireEncodedStream::newPacket, this, &PlasmaScreencastV1Session::onPacketReceived);
         connect(encodedStream, &PipeWireEncodedStream::sizeChanged, this, &PlasmaScreencastV1Session::setSize);
--- a/src/PortalSession.cpp
+++ b/src/PortalSession.cpp
@@ -337,7 +337,10 @@ void PortalSession::start()
             encodedStream->setNodeId(stream.nodeId);
             encodedStream->setFd(fd.takeFileDescriptor());
             encodedStream->setEncodingPreference(PipeWireBaseEncodedStream::EncodingPreference::Speed);
-            // Ensure we encode in full color range so FFmpeg decodes correctly.
-            encodedStream->setColorRange(PipeWireBaseEncodedStream::ColorRange::Full);
+            // Per [MS-RDPEGFX] 3.1.5.5, mstsc decodes the AVC444
+            // H.264 stream as YUV420 *Limited* range. Use Limited
+            // by default; override with KRDP_COLOR_RANGE=full for
+            // FFmpeg-based test clients.
+            encodedStream->setColorRange(qEnvironmentVariable("KRDP_COLOR_RANGE") == QStringLiteral("full")
+                                             ? PipeWireBaseEncodedStream::ColorRange::Full
+                                             : PipeWireBaseEncodedStream::ColorRange::Limited);
             encodedStream->setEncoder(PipeWireEncodedStream::H264Baseline);
             connect(encodedStream, &PipeWireEncodedStream::newPacket, this, &PortalSession::onPacketReceived);
             connect(encodedStream, &PipeWireEncodedStream::sizeChanged, this, &PortalSession::setSize);
